<subSubSection id="C35B6510FFF2FFC15D2BFBB4B41AFB95" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="593" pageId="31" pageNumber="589" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFF2FFFD5D2BFBB4B1EBFB6B" blockId="31.[806,1421,1050,1256]" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFF2FFFD5D2BFBB4B68EFBB3" box="[806,925,1051,1072]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFF2FFFD5B0FFBB5B074FBB3" box="[1282,1383,1050,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halticini">Halticini</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: small, gracile body; rounded head with large eyes; semitranslucent hemelytra; aedeagus with extremely narrow, convoluted ductus seminis, endosoma with irregular sclerotized mass apical to secondary gonopore, possibly formed by multiple strand-like spicules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFF2FFC05D2BFABCB73EF9BF" blockId="31.[806,1421,1299,1903]" lastBlockId="34.[164,778,1513,1596]" lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="592" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFF2FFFD5D2BFABCB6D4FAAB" box="[806,967,1299,1320]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">Redescription:</emphasis>
Small and fragile; macropterous. Coloration (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFF2FFFD5D8AFA9DB6DAFACB" box="[903,969,1330,1352]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[224,1341,194,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-0@11.[218,1349,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Photographs of Halticini genera: Acratheus–Halticus. Abbreviations: F, female; M, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406616/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
): glossy; head, pronotum, and abdomen dark brown, contrasting with mostly pale antennae, hemelytra, and legs. Hemelytra translucent. Surface and vestiture (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFF2FFFD5DD4FA21B133FA20" box="[985,1056,1422,1444]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[224,1341,194,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-0@11.[218,1349,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Photographs of Halticini genera: Acratheus–Halticus. Abbreviations: F, female; M, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406616/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFF2FFFD5A3FFA21B1C1FA20" box="[1074,1234,1422,1443]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="33.[144,223,1566,1585]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-90@33.[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 20. Scanning electron micrograph images of an undescribed species of Dicyphopsis (male). A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, head, anterior view; C, head, ventral view; D, head and thorax, lateral view; E, external efferent system of the metathoracic scent gland; F, tarsus; G, pygophore, lateral view; H, pygophore, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406650/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">20A–D, G, H</figureCitation>
): body sparsely clothed in long pale or dark simple setae and regions of very short, dense, adpressed setae. Head mostly smooth with a few long setae, clypeus and labrum more densely covered with shorter setae; posterior of gena with dense short setae. Antenna clothed in short, slender spine-like setae; 
<collectingRegion id="4985F879FFF2FFFD5AAEF9E9B1ACF9D8" box="[1187,1215,1606,1627]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">AI</collectingRegion>
with a few thin spines, slightly longer than width of segment. Pronotum with sparse covering of longer simple setae, collar with short dense pilosity, thoracic pleura with dense, short pilosity, Hemelytron sparsely covered with long decumbent setae. Femora clothed in long, reclining, simple to weakly spinose setae; tibiae with semi-erect spine-like setae. Structure: head (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFF2FFFD5B4DF8B3B094F8B2" box="[1344,1415,1820,1842]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[224,1341,194,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-0@11.[218,1349,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Photographs of Halticini genera: Acratheus–Halticus. Abbreviations: F, female; M, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406616/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFF2FFFD5D2BF895B66AF8D3" box="[806,889,1850,1872]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="33.[144,223,1566,1585]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-90@33.[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 20. Scanning electron micrograph images of an undescribed species of Dicyphopsis (male). A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, head, anterior view; C, head, ventral view; D, head and thorax, lateral view; E, external efferent system of the metathoracic scent gland; F, tarsus; G, pygophore, lateral view; H, pygophore, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406650/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="589">20A–D</figureCitation>
): rounded, weakly transverse, posterior margin of vertex weakly convex; wider than tall, wider than anterior of pronotum; gena height approximately equal to eye height; eyes rounded, sessile, not touching anterior of pronotum; frons broadly rounded, bulging. Labium (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25C60F9CBB7EDF9FA" box="[621,766,1636,1658]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="33.[144,223,1566,1585]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-90@33.[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 20. Scanning electron micrograph images of an undescribed species of Dicyphopsis (male). A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, head, anterior view; C, head, ventral view; D, head and thorax, lateral view; E, external efferent system of the metathoracic scent gland; F, tarsus; G, pygophore, lateral view; H, pygophore, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406650/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">Fig. 20C, D</figureCitation>
): extends to metacoxae. Antennae (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25C42F92CB785F91B" box="[591,662,1667,1689]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[224,1341,194,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-0@11.[218,1349,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Photographs of Halticini genera: Acratheus–Halticus. Abbreviations: F, female; M, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406616/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25CA3F92CB613F91A" box="[686,768,1667,1689]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="33.[144,223,1566,1585]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-90@33.[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 20. Scanning electron micrograph images of an undescribed species of Dicyphopsis (male). A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, head, anterior view; C, head, ventral view; D, head and thorax, lateral view; E, external efferent system of the metathoracic scent gland; F, tarsus; G, pygophore, lateral view; H, pygophore, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406650/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">20A–D</figureCitation>
): insertion in front of ventral margin of eye; long and thin, 
<collectingRegion id="4985F879FFCDFFC25EE7F96FB415F956" box="[234,262,1728,1749]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">AI</collectingRegion>
slightly longer than eye height. Thorax (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25EA1F971B5E0F977" box="[172,243,1758,1780]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[224,1341,194,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-0@11.[218,1349,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Photographs of Halticini genera: Acratheus–Halticus. Abbreviations: F, female; M, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406616/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25F09F970B44BF977" box="[260,344,1759,1780]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="33.[144,223,1566,1585]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-90@33.[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 20. Scanning electron micrograph images of an undescribed species of Dicyphopsis (male). A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, head, anterior view; C, head, ventral view; D, head and thorax, lateral view; E, external efferent system of the metathoracic scent gland; F, tarsus; G, pygophore, lateral view; H, pygophore, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406650/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">20D, E</figureCitation>
): pronotum trapezoidal, steep, collar broad and flat, callosite region faintly medially depressed, humeral angles rounded, posteriorly deeply depressed, lateral and posterior margins concave; mesoscutum visible; scutellum thin and triangular; metathoracic spiracle small, with narrow band of evaporative bodies above; MTG efferent system narrow and angled posteriorly, ostiole a vertical slit, peritreme tongue-shaped, running along ventral margin of tergite, bordered above by narrow band of evaporative bodies. Hemelytra (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25B07F90EB05EF934" box="[1290,1357,1697,1719]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[224,1341,194,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-0@11.[218,1349,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Photographs of Halticini genera: Acratheus–Halticus. Abbreviations: F, female; M, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406616/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
): semitranslucent, lateral margins parallel, cuneus long and narrow, membrane extends beyond abdomen. Legs (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25D4FF952B69AF891" box="[834,905,1789,1811]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="11.[144,223,1824,1843]" captionTargetBox="[224,1341,194,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-0@11.[218,1349,194,1794]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 3. Photographs of Halticini genera: Acratheus–Halticus. Abbreviations: F, female; M, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406616" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406616/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">Figs 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25D92F952B10CF891" box="[927,1055,1789,1810]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="33.[144,223,1566,1585]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-90@33.[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 20. Scanning electron micrograph images of an undescribed species of Dicyphopsis (male). A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, head, anterior view; C, head, ventral view; D, head and thorax, lateral view; E, external efferent system of the metathoracic scent gland; F, tarsus; G, pygophore, lateral view; H, pygophore, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406650/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">20A, B, F</figureCitation>
): long and slender; metafemur slightly incrassate; pretarsi without fleshy pulvilli. Abdomen: narrow, parallel-sided, in males slightly broadened at pygophore. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCDFFC25B1DF8F6B08EF8ED" box="[1296,1437,1881,1903]" captionStart="Figure 20" captionStartId="33.[144,223,1566,1585]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetId="figure-90@33.[303,1263,195,1536]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 20. Scanning electron micrograph images of an undescribed species of Dicyphopsis (male). A, head and thorax, dorsal view; B, head, anterior view; C, head, ventral view; D, head and thorax, lateral view; E, external efferent system of the metathoracic scent gland; F, tarsus; G, pygophore, lateral view; H, pygophore, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406650/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="590">Figs 20G, H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCCFFC35E9DF90EB5F3F934" box="[144,224,1697,1719]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="34.[164,243,1377,1396]" captionTargetBox="[335,1281,195,1338]" captionTargetId="figure-173@34.[323,1283,194,1347]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figure 21. Male and female genitalia of an unidentified species of Dicyphopsis. A, aedeagus; B, left paramere; C, right paramere; D, bursa copulatrix, ventral view; E, posterior wall; F, first gonapophyses, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406652" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406652/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="591">21A–C</figureCitation>
): pygophore conical; left paramere L-shaped, sensory lobe broad, apophysis short, tapering, with small subapical keel, apically hooked; right paramere longer than left, straight, spoon-shaped; phallotheca elongate-oval, simple; ductus seminis elongate and constricted, with flexible ribbing; secondary gonopore ill defined, weakly sclerotized; endosoma large, with broad, irregular sclerotized mass near secondary gonopore, possibly made of many long, thin sclerites. Female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="137A2A1EFFCCFFC35A01F971B19CF976" box="[1036,1167,1758,1781]" captionStart="Figure 21" captionStartId="34.[164,243,1377,1396]" captionTargetBox="[335,1281,195,1338]" captionTargetId="figure-173@34.[323,1283,194,1347]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figure 21. Male and female genitalia of an unidentified species of Dicyphopsis. A, aedeagus; B, left paramere; C, right paramere; D, bursa copulatrix, ventral view; E, posterior wall; F, first gonapophyses, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406652" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406652/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="591">Fig. 21D–F</figureCitation>
): DLP membranous, sclerotized rings transverse, medially subcontiguous, subrectangulate, very weakly sclerotized; VLP simple, with medial margin sclerotized and dentate; posterior wall of bursa copulatrix weakly sclerotized anteriorly, medially with fields of spines, anteriorly with faint bilateral swellings; margins of vestibulum symmetrical with very weak sclerotization.
</paragraph>
