<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFCFFFC05EA9F9DCB618F880" blockId="34.[164,779,1651,1795]" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCFFFC05EA9F9DCB77AF90B" box="[164,617,1651,1672]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">
Diversity and distribution: 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCFFFC05FECF9DCB77AF90B" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[481,617,1651,1672]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Dicyphopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dicyphopsis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
includes only one described species from 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFCFFFC05FFEF93EB74EF924" box="[499,605,1681,1703]" name="Tanzania" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4985F879FFCFFFC05C7FF93EB7ECF924" box="[626,767,1681,1703]" country="Tanzania" name="Kilimanjaro" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Kilimanjaro</collectingRegion>
), though undescribed specimens matching the original description and considered congeneric have been collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFCFFFC05F00F942B45AF880" box="[269,329,1773,1795]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Zaire</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFCFFFC05F8EF942B4C3F880" box="[387,464,1773,1795]" name="Ghana" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Ghana</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCFFFC05FD2F942B7ECF880" author="Kerzhner IM &amp; Schuh RT" box="[479,767,1773,1795]" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref45917" refString="Kerzhner IM, Schuh RT. 1995. Homonymy, synonymy, and new combinations in the Miridae (Heteroptera). American Museum Novitates 3137: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1995">Kerzhner &amp; Schuh, 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFCFFFC05EA9F895B497F8EC" blockId="34.[164,778,1850,1903]" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCFFFC05EA9F895B460F8D3" box="[164,371,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Included species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCFFFC05F86F895B5C8F8ED" authority="Poppius, 1914" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Dicyphopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCFFFC05F86F895B782F8D3" box="[395,657,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Dicyphopsis nigriceps</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCFFFC05CA4F895B5C8F8ED" author="Poppius B" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref47641" refString="Poppius B. 1914. Die Miriden der Athiopischen Region II - Macrolophinae, Heterotominae, Phylinae. Acta Societatis Scientarum Fennicae 44: 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="1914">Poppius, 1914</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingRegion id="4985F879FFCFFFC05EFEF8F6B493F8EC" box="[243,384,1881,1903]" country="Tanzania" name="Kilimanjaro" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Kilimanjaro</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE369BFFCFFFC15D37FA46B41AFB95" blockId="34.[826,1441,1513,1902]" lastBlockId="35.[144,759,198,1046]" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="593" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCFFFC05D37FA46B6B5FA7D" box="[826,934,1513,1534]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Remarks:</emphasis>
The monotypic genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCFFFC05AD4FA46B072FA7D" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[1241,1377,1513,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Dicyphopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCFFFC05AD4FA46B072FA7D" box="[1241,1377,1513,1534]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Dicyphopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single female specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCFFFC05B4DF9A7B66FF9BF" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Dicyphopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriceps">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCFFFC05B4DF9A7B66FF9BF" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Dic. nigriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFCFFFC05A00F989B164F9BF" box="[1037,1143,1574,1596]" name="Tanzania" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCFFFC05A8BF989B039F9BF" author="Poppius B" box="[1158,1322,1574,1596]" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref47641" refString="Poppius B. 1914. Die Miriden der Athiopischen Region II - Macrolophinae, Heterotominae, Phylinae. Acta Societatis Scientarum Fennicae 44: 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="1914">Poppius, 1914</bibRefCitation>
). Unfortunately the 
<typeStatus id="54FA8839FFCFFFC05DB8F9EBB105F9D9" box="[949,1046,1604,1626]" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">holotype</typeStatus>
was destroyed during shipment to G. Cassis (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCFFFC05DB2F9CCB146F9FA" author="Cassis G" box="[959,1109,1635,1657]" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" refId="ref42871" refString="Cassis G. 1986. A systematic study of the subfamily Dicyphinae (Heteroptera: Miridae). PhD Dissertation. Oregon State University, Corvallis." type="book" year="1986">Cassis, 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCFFFC05A6AF9CCB087F9FA" author="Kerzhner IM &amp; Schuh RT" box="[1127,1428,1635,1657]" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref45917" refString="Kerzhner IM, Schuh RT. 1995. Homonymy, synonymy, and new combinations in the Miridae (Heteroptera). American Museum Novitates 3137: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1995">Kerzhner &amp; Schuh, 1995</bibRefCitation>
), leaving no existing specimens of this species. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCFFFC05B5EF92DB10FF935" author="Kerzhner IM &amp; Schuh RT" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref45917" refString="Kerzhner IM, Schuh RT. 1995. Homonymy, synonymy, and new combinations in the Miridae (Heteroptera). American Museum Novitates 3137: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1995">Kerzhner &amp; Schuh (1995)</bibRefCitation>
identified a number of specimens that they considered congeneric (although not conspecific) collected in 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFCFFFC05A0AF972B150F970" box="[1031,1091,1757,1779]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Zaire</collectingCountry>
by N. A. Weber in 1948, and 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFCFFFC05D37F953B694F891" box="[826,903,1788,1810]" name="Ghana" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Ghana</collectingCountry>
by R. T. Schuh and J. A. Slater in 1967. We have only seen the 
<collectingCountry id="F356760BFFCFFFC05A2BF8B4B160F8B2" box="[1062,1139,1819,1841]" name="Ghana" pageId="34" pageNumber="592">Ghana</collectingCountry>
specimens, and although the habitus is not typical of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCFFFC05ACCF896B03BF8CC" box="[1217,1320,1849,1871]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halticini">Halticini</taxonomicName>
, we agree with their assertion that the genitalia is of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCFFFC15B62F8F7B5D8FF5F" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="593" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="592" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halticini">Halticini</taxonomicName>
type, albeit with some minor differences. Most notably, in the aedeagus the ductus seminis is extremely narrow, and the spicule form is unique. In the female however, the margins of the vestibulum are symmetrical, a character consistent throughout the tribe. It is worth noting that what we call 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15CB1FEF0B5F5FE11" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Dicyphopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCEFFC15CB1FEF0B5F5FE11" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="593">Dicyphopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially appears identical to what 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCEFFC15CCAFED2B42CFE31" author="Linnavuori RE" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref46937" refString="Linnavuori RE. 1994. Orthotylinae of West, Central and North-East Africa (Heteroptera, Miridae). Acta Zoologica Fennica 193: 1 - 84." type="journal article" year="1994">Linnavuori (1994)</bibRefCitation>
identifies as the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15C29FE33B7B7FE31" authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1916" box="[548,676,412,434]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Orthotylini">Orthotylini</taxonomicName>
genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15E9DFE14B46CFE52" authority="Poppius" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[144,383,443,465]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Nycticapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCEFFC15E9DFE14B40BFE53" box="[144,280,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="593">Nycticapsus</emphasis>
Poppius
</taxonomicName>
(D. Forero, pers. comm.). Both genera were described in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCEFFC15FBFFE76B74DFE6C" author="Poppius B" box="[434,606,473,495]" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref47641" refString="Poppius B. 1914. Die Miriden der Athiopischen Region II - Macrolophinae, Heterotominae, Phylinae. Acta Societatis Scientarum Fennicae 44: 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="1914">Poppius (1914)</bibRefCitation>
, with neither one illustrated. As we have not seen specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15E9DFDB8B40BFDAF" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[144,280,535,556]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Nycticapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCEFFC15E9DFDB8B40BFDAF" box="[144,280,535,556]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="593">Nycticapsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for the moment we do not know whether Poppius described the same species twice, whether Linnavuori misidentified specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15C44FDFBB7C2FDEA" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[585,721,596,617]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Dicyphopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCEFFC15C44FDFBB7C2FDEA" box="[585,721,596,617]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="593">Dicyphopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or whether these are in fact distinct genera. As the genitalia are clearly of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15FDCFD3EB725FD24" box="[465,566,657,679]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Halticini">Halticini</taxonomicName>
rather than the 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15E9DFD00B403FD46" authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1916" box="[144,272,687,709]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Orthotylini">Orthotylini</taxonomicName>
type, we retain 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B6AFFCEFFC15FF4FD00B5C4FD67" author="Kerzhner IM &amp; Schuh RT" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref45917" refString="Kerzhner IM, Schuh RT. 1995. Homonymy, synonymy, and new combinations in the Miridae (Heteroptera). American Museum Novitates 3137: 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1995">Kerzhner &amp; Schuh’s (1995)</bibRefCitation>
initial placement of these specimens. Phylogenetic analysis places 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15F89FD42B71FFC81" authorityName="Poppius" authorityYear="1914" box="[388,524,749,770]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Dicyphopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCEFFC15F89FD42B71FFC81" box="[388,524,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="593">Dicyphopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a clade of primarily African taxa, defined by the presence of paired bilateral pillow-like swellings on the posterior wall (87-1). These taxa also share similar metathoracic scent gland structure, with the peritreme finger-like, angled back and resting along the caudal margin of the metepimeron (25-3), a condition shared only by 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15E9DFC6CB430FC5B" authorityName="Horvath" authorityYear="1877" box="[144,291,963,984]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Piezocranum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCEFFC15E9DFC6CB430FC5B" box="[144,291,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="593">Piezocranum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15F64FC6CB4EAFC5B" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1862" box="[361,505,963,984]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Coridromius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCEFFC15F64FC6CB4EAFC5B" box="[361,505,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="593">Coridromius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(could not be determined in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D18FFCEFFC15F03FC4DB4D8FC74" authorityName="Schuh" authorityYear="1974" box="[270,459,994,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Namaquacapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="593" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935EA89FFCEFFC15F03FC4DB4D8FC74" box="[270,459,994,1015]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="593">Namaquacapsus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of condition of specimen).
